  "text": "Case Material Polymer and steel; polymer and titanium Case size 42mm, 47mm, 51mm Colors Silver, Gray, Gold, Black Display AMOLED Storage 16 GB; 32 GB The Garmin Epix Pro is a fantastic smartwatch for active users. It offers exercise and advanced sleep tracking for all phases of activity. It's now at its lowest price yet at $410 off. You can't go wrong with a Garmin smartwatch if you're looking to get an impressive wearable that does a fantastic job of tracking your health and fitness metrics. Not only that, but most Garmin smartwatches offer incredible battery life, along with other bells and whistles as well. The Epix Pro (2nd Gen) is one of our favorite smartwatches out right now, offering a premium experience that can't be ignored. Related Garmin Epix Pro (Gen 2) review: It's worth the money The second-gen Epix Pro brings some welcomed changes And while this particular model has a retail price of $1,100, you can now score a hefty discount that knocks $410 off, dropping it down to its lowest price to date at $690. You won't find a better price than what we're seeing now. And you also won't regret picking this model up if you're looking to really get a better grasp of your daily workouts. What's great about the Garmin Epix Pro (Gen 2)? The first thing you should probably know about this watch is that it is a bit larger, coming in at 51mm. However, you also get a large and beautiful AMOLED screen, along with an impressive battery life that can last up to 31 days. In addition, the watch is built to be extremely durable, with a fiber-reinforced polymer case, titanium rear cover, and sapphire screen. It should come as no surprise that the watch has a wealth of sensors, making it possible to track the most important details of your workout. And there's even a Garmin Coach that can help you train better, in order to meet your specific goals. Furthermore, you can also get GPS tracking for your runs, walks, or even hikes. And there's built-in safety and tracking features as well. Since this is a smartwatch, you'll be able to get notifications on your wrist, and be able to make payments at compatible tap to pay terminals as well. Overall, this watch really does it all and makes it easy to track your health and fitness metrics that matter. Get it now for its best price yet while this deal's still around. Smartwatches \u0026 Wearables Garmin Epix Pro (2nd Gen)",
